title: hollow earth theory
description:
the theory seems absurd at first glance, like the theory about a spherical earth seemed to people in the 15th century. At further inspection there is much to it.
Consider how easy it could be disproved: Take a few snapshots off a satellite that is near each pole (or hole, for that matter), and let those snapshots clearly show the icecaps on the poles without cloud-cover. 
This should be as easy as - say - taking snapshozs from the stars when on the moon (the equipment for that purpose would weigh considerably less than a totally unnecessary moonrover, which they took purportedly to the moon), such pictures would have proven once and for all the authenticity of the manned moon-landings, for they could not have been faked on earth - but that is another story.
Anyway, until proven wrong by said photographs I will adher to this theory.
